DEBUG:openai._base_client:Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-05b212a1-33ec-401a-bc24-0c2dce90a4f8', 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'system', 'content': "You are an expert change management consultant. Generate personalized responses to stakeholder concerns based on their mental model, project context, and communication preferences. Respond with JSON in this format: {'suggested_response': 'response text', 'tone_notes': 'communication guidance', 'key_points': ['point1', 'point2']}"}, {'role': 'user', 'content': "\nSTAKEHOLDER CONCERN:\nWill I lose my desk?\n\nSTAKEHOLDER MENTAL MODEL: Adaptive Navigator\nDescription: You're flexible and intuitive, helping others navigate change with confidence.\nStrengths: Highly adaptable to changing circumstances, Strong intuition for reading situations, Helps others feel comfortable with uncertainty, Balances multiple perspectives effectively\nChallenges: May lack consistency in approach, Could struggle to provide clear direction, Might avoid making firm commitments\nRecommendations: Develop a personal framework for decision-making, Practice articulating your intuitive insights, Set clear boundaries and expectations, Use your adaptability to model resilience for others\n\nPROJECT CONTEXT:\nProject Name: Office Move\nDescription: Moving Office in 2025\n\nCHANGE STRATEGY:\nPREPARED\r\nLeadership readiness\r\nBriefed ELT on relocation goals, risks, and key milestones\r\nAppointed a relocation sponsor with clear accountability\r\nEmbedded move into broader operational strategy and BAU plans\r\nProject governance\r\nEstablished cross-functional relocation working group\r\nDefined decision rights and escalation pathways\r\nWeekly check-ins scheduled for executive oversight\r\nResource planning\r\nIdentified internal capability needs for facilities, IT, and communications\r\nSecured budget for fit-out, logistics, and transitional support\r\nConfirmed legal, lease, and compliance obligations\r\n\r\nAWARE\r\nCommunication strategy\r\nDeveloped a clear narrative: why, what, when, how\r\nMapped stakeholder groups and tailored key messages\r\n\r\nLaunched regular updates via email, intranet, and huddles\r\nEmployee engagement\r\nAnnounced change early with Q&A forums to reduce uncertainty\r\nInvited early feedback on workspace preferences (e.g. survey or workshop)\r\nShared floorplans, amenities, and local services in advance\r\nExternal awareness\r\nNotified suppliers, clients, and partners with new contact details\r\nUpdated address on digital channels ahead of move\r\nPlanned soft launch events for key clients and partners\r\n\r\nSUPPORTED\r\nTraining & onboarding\r\nProvided training for new systems (e.g. booking desks, access cards)\r\nDelivered induction tours during relocation week\r\nPrepared FAQs and troubleshooting guides for transition phase\r\nSystems & tools readiness\r\nConfirmed IT infrastructure migration plan and test schedule\r\nEnsured hybrid work tools functional from day one\r\nDistributed new desk equipment or accessories as needed\r\nPeople-centred transition\r\nOffered relocation support for vulnerable or affected staff (e.g. transport subsidies)\r\nAllowed flexible WFH days around move period\r\nSet up “Move Ambassadors” to guide and assist peers\r\n\r\nCOMMITTED\r\nFeedback and check-in loops\r\nScheduled pulse checks post-move at weeks 2, 6, and 12\r\nEmbedded feedback channels into BAU (e.g. Yammer, lunch & learns)\r\nPublished transparent progress reports on post-move actions\r\nLeadership visibility\r\nLeaders to work from new office regularly in first 90 days\r\nSenior team to host welcome-back breakfasts in first two weeks\r\nSponsor to send fortnightly personal updates on progress\r\nCulture and connection\r\nCurated team-building events in new space to re-anchor culture\r\nReinforced shared behaviours aligned with SynergyIQ values\r\nUsed the move as an opportunity to reframe team identity and collaboration norms\r\n\r\n📏 Measures & Outcomes\r\nPrepared\r\n% of leaders attending readiness sessions\r\nOn-time completion of governance milestones\r\n\r\nAware\r\nEmployee awareness score (via comms pulse)\r\nEngagement with move communications (open rates, forum attendance)\r\n\r\nSupported\r\nIT and facilities fault rates post-move\r\nSatisfaction with induction resources\r\n% of employees reporting ease of transition\r\n\r\nCommitted\r\nPost-move engagement score\r\nRetention of team rituals and connection indicators\r\nVolume and sentiment of feedback submissions\n\nKEY MESSAGES:\nCore Narrative\r\n“We’re moving forward together.”\r\nThis office relocation is a strategic step to support our next phase of growth, collaboration, and innovation.\r\n\r\n“Our new space reflects how we work best.”\r\nDesigned with flexibility, wellbeing, and connection in mind, the new office supports hybrid work and empowers teams to thrive.\r\n\r\n“You are part of the journey.”\r\nYour input, ideas, and feedback are helping shape how we move — physically and culturally — into the new space.\r\n\r\nAwareness & Engagement\r\n“You’ll know what’s happening, when, and why.”\r\nWe’re committed to keeping everyone informed with clear, timely updates through multiple channels.\r\n\r\n“Have your say.”\r\nWe’re inviting your feedback on workspace features, team needs, and the move experience — and acting on what we hear.\r\n\r\n“This move affects all of us — and benefits all of us.”\r\nWhether you’re in the office often or occasionally, we’re making sure the space supports your role, your rhythm, and your team.\r\n\r\nSupport & Transition\r\n“We’re not just moving desks — we’re setting you up to succeed.”\r\nFrom IT to coffee machines, everything is being planned to reduce friction and support a smooth transition.\r\n\r\n“Help is close at hand.”\r\nOur Move Ambassadors, onboarding guides, and help channels are here to support you every step of the way.\r\n\r\n“Flexibility matters.”\r\nWe’re giving you space and time to adjust, with work-from-home options and practical support during the transition period.\r\n\r\nCommitment & Momentum\r\n“This is a new chapter, not just a new address.”\r\nLet’s use this opportunity to reimagine how we collaborate, connect, and work together with purpose.\r\n\r\n“Leadership is with you — and in it with you.”\r\nLeaders will be present, visible, and available during and after the move.\r\n\r\n“We’re learning as we go — and improving as we move.”\r\nYour feedback shapes how we continue to refine the space and our experience in it.\n\nIMPORTANT DATES:\nProject Start: May 10, 2025\nCommunication Start: May 27, 2025\nGo Live Date: August 15, 2025\nAssessment End: September 01, 2025\n\nEXISTING FAQ CONTENT:\nQ: What will be the future printing options?\nA: We're not sure yet, Ray is looking into options for a new printer.\n\nQ: What's the new address?\nA: Naylor House, corner of Pirie and Flinders Street\n\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Address the specific concern directly and personally\n2. Use the stakeholder's mental model to tailor your communication approach\n3. Reference relevant project information, strategy, and key messages\n4. Include specific dates when relevant\n5. Match the tone and style that resonates with this mental model\n6. Keep the response professional but approachable\n7. Provide actionable information where possible\n8. Ensure the response addresses their underlying motivators and concerns\n\nGenerate a suggested response that the change manager can review and edit before sending.\n"}], 'model': 'gpt-4o', 'max_tokens': 1000, 'response_format': {'type': 'json_object'}}}
